{
  "title": "Create cloud carbon footprint reports from Power BI",
  "content": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\">\n<div></div>\n<p>You may create a cloud carbon footprint report from Power BI. The following example shows how to create a simple cloud report.</p>\n<h2 id=\"Use_case\"><a id=\"Use_case\" name=\"Use_case\" title=\"Use case\"></a>Use case</h2>\n<p>Your organization wants to create a cloud report that reflects the Azure emissions over time.</p>\n<p>To create the cloud report from Power BI, perform the following steps.</p>\n<h3 id=\"Connect_to_the_OData_feed\"><a id=\"Connect_to_the_database\" name=\"Connect_to_the_database\" title=\"Connect to the database\"></a>Connect to the database</h3>\n<ol style=\"padding-left: 0px;\"><li style=\"--number-width: 10px; --number-spacing: 24px; margin-left: 36px; position: relative;\">Open Power BI Desktop. On the <strong>Home</strong> page, select <strong>Get data</strong><b> &gt; More…</b><br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBICloudCarbonReport1.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/4/47/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport1.png\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport1_78a79f1a.png\" style=\"width: 306.126px; height: 800px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\"/> </a></li><li style=\"--number-width: 13px; --number-spacing: 24px; margin-left: 36px; position: relative;\">In the <strong>Get Data</strong> window, select <strong>Database</strong>, and then select <strong>Vertica </strong>from the database list. Then, click <strong>Connect</strong>.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBICloudCarbonReport2.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/a/ad/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport2.png\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport2_be7feecd.png\" style=\"width:800px;height:777px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\"/> </a></li><li style=\"--number-width: 13px; --number-spacing: 24px; margin-left: 36px; position: relative;\">Enter the Vertica server address and the database name, and then select <strong>Import </strong>as <strong>Data connectivity mode</strong>. Then, click <strong>OK</strong>.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBICloudCarbonReport3.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/f/f7/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport3.png\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport3_83f6e063.png\" style=\"width:800px;height:368px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\"/> </a></li><li style=\"--number-width: 13px; --number-spacing: 24px; margin-left: 36px; position: relative;\">Now, you're connected to the Cloud Cost Reporting database. Power BI Desktop displays the available tables and other data elements in the <strong>Navigator</strong> window.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBICloudCarbonReport4.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/8/82/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport4.png\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport4_820b52c4.png\" style=\"width:800px;height:638px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\"/> </a></li><li style=\"--number-width: 12px; --number-spacing: 24px; margin-left: 36px; position: relative;\">Expand the schema of your Azure DB and select the <strong>CLOUD_AZURE_CARBON_EMISSIONS_1M</strong> view. Click the <strong>Load </strong>button to load the carbon footprint data.\n\t<p>Once all the data is loaded, the Azure view appears in the side panel.</p>\n<div><a class=\"image\" href=\"\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBICloudCarbonReport7.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/0/0d/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport7.png\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport7_32af0620.png\" style=\"width:400px;height:345px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\"/> </a></div>\n</li></ol>\n<h3 id=\"Create_the_report\"><a id=\"Create_the_cloud_report\" name=\"Create_the_cloud_report\" title=\"Create the cloud report\"></a>Create the cloud report</h3>\n<ol style=\"padding-left: 0px;\"><li style=\"--number-width: 10px; --number-spacing: 24px; margin-left: 36px; position: relative;\">Select <strong>Table </strong>from the <strong>Visualizations </strong>panel.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBIODataCase6.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/8/8b/SMAXBIODataCase6.png\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBIODataCase6_dfc78945.png\" style=\"width:232px;height:400px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\"/> </a></li><li style=\"--number-width: 13px; --number-spacing: 24px; margin-left: 36px; position: relative;\">Select the <strong>co2e </strong>and <strong>timestamp </strong>fields from the <strong>CLOUD_AZURE_CARBON_EMISSIONS_1M </strong>view.<br/>\n\tNow, you see a table that displays the selected fields.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBICloudCarbonReport9.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/4/4d/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport9.png\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport9_b11de35f.png\" style=\"width:266px;height:280px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\"/> </a></li><li style=\"--number-width: 13px; --number-spacing: 24px; margin-left: 36px; position: relative;\">In the <strong>Data </strong>side panel, uncheck <strong>Quarter </strong>and <strong>Day</strong>.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBICloudCarbonReport10.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/f/f8/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport10.png\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport10_5e36a497.png\" style=\"width: 658.177px; height: 800px; margin: 0px; border: 0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\"/> </a><br/>\n\tNow, the table displays <strong>Sum of co2e</strong>, <strong>Year</strong>,<strong> </strong>and <strong>Month</strong>. <br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBICloudCarbonReport11.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/a/a7/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport11.png\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport11_3d855ad6.png\" style=\"width:210px;height:300px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\"/> </a></li><li style=\"--number-width: 13px; --number-spacing: 24px; margin-left: 36px; position: relative;\">Select the entire table. You can see the focus indicators when the whole table is selected. Then, select<strong> Line chart </strong>in the <strong>Visualizations </strong>panel.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBICloudCarbonReport12.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/4/4d/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport12.png\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport12_ee8d75c6.png\" style=\"width:226px;height:386px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\"/> </a><br/>\n\tNow, the table is converted into a line chart.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBICloudCarbonReport13.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/9/9c/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport13.png\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport13_d6714d96.png\" style=\"width:554px;height:282px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\"/> </a></li><li style=\"--number-width: 12px; --number-spacing: 24px; margin-left: 36px; position: relative;\">You may notice that some of the labels on the chart aren't clear or easy to understand. You can rename them in the <strong>Visualizations</strong> panel:<br/>\n\tClick <strong>Sum of co2e</strong> from <strong>Y-aixs</strong> and then select <strong>Rename for this visual</strong>. You may rename the label as <strong>MTCO2e</strong>, which is the unit of carbon emissions.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBICloudCarbonReport14.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/c/cb/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport14.png\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport14_f4d21910.png\" style=\"width:430px;height:469px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\"/> </a></li><li style=\"--number-width: 12px; --number-spacing: 24px; margin-left: 36px; position: relative;\">In the <strong>Visualizations </strong>panel, switch to <strong>Format your visual</strong>. Expand <strong>Title </strong>under the <strong>General </strong>tab, and then set the <strong>Text </strong>field to <strong>Azure emissions over time</strong>.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBICloudCarbonReport15.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/1/13/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport15.png\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport15_161805d2.png\" style=\"width:236px;height:594px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\"/> </a><br/>\n\tNow, the chart looks like below.<br/>\n<a class=\"image\" href=\"\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBICloudCarbonReport16.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/f/fb/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport16.png\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport16_ea15290b.png\" style=\"width:554px;height:281px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\"/> </a></li></ol>\n<h3><a id=\"Refresh_the_data\" name=\"Refresh_the_data\" title=\"Refresh the data\"></a>Refresh the data</h3>\n<p>When the data is updated in the Cloud Cost Reporting database, you need to refresh the data in Power BI to synchronize the changes.</p>\n<p>For each file, select <strong>More options</strong> and then select <strong>Refresh data</strong>. The chart will be refreshed accordingly.</p>\n<div><a class=\"image\" href=\"\"> <img alt=\"SMAXBICloudCarbonReport17.png\" border=\"0\" file=\"https://staging.docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/0/05/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport17.png\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"../../../images/SMAXBICloudCarbonReport17_d28355cf.png\" style=\"width:521px;height:621px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;border:0px solid black;\" vspace=\"0\"/> </a></div>\n</div>",
